caption: Try the French dip, banh mi, and the jalapeno fries!
Weekend special with with awesome burgers & CRINKLE FRIES! it was busy but order by phone so pickup was faster 👍🏼
They were ok. Bread for french dip was burnt, so it was very chewy. I don't plan on returning.
E.A.R.L sandwiches is awesome. I highly recommend the cubano.

I was let down today by E.A.R.L. I was not going to write a bad review but once I opened up my togo box and seen the sandwich I was forced to express how I feel. This place used to be amazing with amazing looking sandwiches. I phoned in an order for 2 sandwiches with a side of fries. I arrived and they said they were out of fries. Honestly the only reason I go to E.A.R.L is for the fries. I asked when they ran out and the response was "Yesterday". I wish I was told that over the phone before I drove 20 minutes out of my way. Once i got to my office and opened up my sandwich I was very disappointed it reminded me of a McDonald's style sandwich  only it cost me 15 bucks. Not sure if I'll ever go back. It's hard to write a bad review about a restaurant during Covid but it's also hard paying 15 bucks for A Mc Chicken with cheese during Covid.  I just found a hair in my sandwich... Done.

Quite possibly the best sandwiches in our entire lives (Fun Goat and Fried Chicken Po Boy). Bread not too hard, not too soft; meats, cheeses, sauces and veggies all superb. Bacon Cheese Fries had proper amount of sauce over KRINKLE fries- yes, please!!! We will be back!

One of the best sandwich spots in Honolulu, a big 👍🏽👍🏽. Great staff and service. This place just checks all the important boxes.  Their spicy chicken sandwich and unique take on a Cubano is off the charts. Also tried many of their other awesome sandwiches and they always have me craving for more
God sandwich
The lobster roll was amazing, I wish I had the option to get the sandwich by itself. I didn't care much for the pasta salad.
Good  food! Delicious.

Probably one of the best burgers I’ve ever had! Pastrami, wagyu patty, cheese, pickles and a side of crinkle cut fries. Had outside seating and was worth the wait! I’ll be back for sure to try the other items on the menu.
Theyre getting uh little too creative with the sandwich ingredients. Tasting all kinds of stuff and didnt go well together. Good service tho!

I was skeptical of the social media recommendation.. however after following him on social media and his presentation sold me. So, today my husband and I went to get the crab cake sandwich. A bit shocked by the price but once we arrived home and took a bite into the sandwiches. It took me back to Maryland! We will be back to try other things off the menu. keep it up!  Uh I was excited to try the Philly, but I was underwhelmed. Where is green peppers and mushrooms ?! I made better homemade and at when I ate at Charley’s.
best sandwiches I've ever had

2021 Update: the menu is different but still delicious (best sandwiches on island) and their customer service is still OUTSTANDING 💕🙏🏽💯 I love these guys!  The vegan sandwich options delicious! The service is also super friendly and helpful. Gotta come back for those garlic fries that I kept seeing pass me by... they looked and smelled ridiculous!
Amazing sandwiches and their Maryland crab cakes are to die for
Great food and service, a little pricy but still great food!!
The food was delicious, tasted fresh but the bread was really tough . You definitely need a dipping sauce with your sandwich to loosen up the bread .
Some of the best sammies in Hawaii.
Must go. Get the spicy chicken sandwich! It was unreal. Bread was also crisped perfectly
Hands down best lunch in town
Spicy chicken sub was extremely good and big enough for two people. Great quality and flavors combined.
Great sandwiches. Loved the Italian!
Whoever gave this place less than five stars doesn’t know what good food is
Love the Drew
Great crew and yummy food!

Their Pastrami sandwich $13 has thick hanburge, bacon, pastrami, cheese and cucumber in it. Very big portion for two ppl. I also ordered $24 Lobster roll. It was portion down, the price went up from $22. Felt it's pricy.
Everything was amazing! 🍞 pudding, 🍫 nut 🍪, turkey salad sandwich, garlic 🍟, and all 3 drinks mixed together!

Holy Cr@p! These sandwiches are awesome. A little on the high side moneywise but could easily make two meals if you aren't supper hungry. They've changed their menu a bit so if you haven't gone for a while, make another visit.
Always amazing food, excellent service and happy people.
Great tasty sandwiches, the bread is perfect
delicious sanwiches

The cubano is terrific. Right away you get a huge hit of the slow cooked pork. You can taste the sharpness of the melted cheese, and the pickle tops everything off. For sure, I would get another.  Service wasn't so great though.

I'm not sure what is going on here today, but out of the like 10 items on the menu they were out of 5 of them. I opted for the beet sandwich for them to tell me they are no longer carrying beets.? Ok, well, can you put avocados in place of the beets? There is an extra charge foe the avocados....lillikoi lemonade.? Oh, no sorry we are out if that too. So $16 for a tea and sandwich.

We ordered the Italian and the Drew. Far and away the best sandwiches we've had on the island, and truthfully stands up to the best sandwich shops we've been to in any of your token cities. Bread is incredible, meat selection is top notch, and they really do special things to their flavor combinations. Each sandwich is totally unique from the next and equally delicious. Anything you choose you'll be completely satisfied with. To say we are impressed is a criminal understatement.

BEST SANDWICHES ON OAHU. and the best sandwiches I’ve ever had and I’m not normally a huge sandwich person. Their French dip is INSANE. Already had it twice within the past week. Their po boi chicken sandwich is also unreal. For non-meat eaters or looking for something a little lighter, the fun beet is super fresh and delicious. The lilikoi lemonade is perfect too. It’s not too sweet. The garlic fries were the only downside, they were good but because we can only do take out right now, they got soggy and mushy so I bet they would be better fresh and eaten right away. Can’t recommend this place enough. The staff is friendly and pretty quick service.
Excellent beef brisket sandwiches. I like the restaurant in Kaimuki better.
Best sandwiches in town love it❤❤❤

The dining area seating could use some improvement and the ticket times were 20-25 minutes BUT...THE SANDWICHES ARE AMAZING!! I had the Chopped Cheese and my wife had the Po’ Boy. I would go back in the hopes they cleaned the tables a little more and the ticket times were improved.

Called in a phone order and the guy said it would be about 20 min. Got there in 10 min waited in line 10 min and paid for the food. Waited another 25 min still no food. I actually work across the street and had to go to work so my boyfriend stayed and waited. He didn’t get the order until another 15 min when he actually walked up to the register and asked if it was almost done. The guy at the front looked at a order that we saw sitting there for a while and said oh there it is. You’d think if we paid and you saw us standing there for a while you would check on it. My boyfriend got to my work a little over an hour later from the time we placed the phone order. We opened the bag only to find out they had given him the wrong order...which wouldn’t have been a big deal if I wasn’t pescatarian and all the sandwiches were of course meat :( So he had to walk back and let them know in which they remade our correct order and the manager was very apologetic and gave him a card for a free sandwich. I really like their shrimp avocado toast so I’m sure I’ll be back. I just hope they can figure out a better system for orders.
Yummy sandwiches.  Elevated quality Sammie's that are filling but also a little pricier than Subway.
Great sandwiches!  Everything I have eaten here is delicious.  The bread is perfectly sized and toasted just right - crunchy but still a bit soft.  Flavor combinations are outstanding.

BAM! This is not your parents place for sandwiches.  This place is tops for unique sandwich choices. The Chicken Poi Boy is amazing. One HUGE sandwich. Flavors galore. The garlic fries are incredible. If you dare save room for dessert - get the chocolate brownie with bacon crumbles.  Can’t wait to try another sandwich!!!

The fried chicken po' boy was the bomb. Crispy chicken, spicy sauce which isn't too spicy. We shared a sandwich and both left satisfied. We have our eyes on a couple other sandwiches for our next visit. The original E.A.R.L in Kaimuki has a slightly different menu. Worth a look

I was really pleased with this place. Came here on a whim and ordered the chicken po boy and the sandwich was amazing. I got the meal deal with lemonade and the potato salad and everything had a good, fresh taste to it. The chicken was white meat and was really flavorful and juicy. They have a lot of options for their sandwiches and don't be afraid to ask questions, the staff will help you decide based on what you are feeling. Recommend giving them a try!
Awesome sandwiches with awesome side dips/sauces!  My favourite is the beer braised brisket.
Best sandwiches that I know of

The food was great. Had the pastrami, and spicy chicken... And garlic fries... Way too much food, but I couldn't decide on which sandwich to buy. Both were delicious. Happy to have found this place within walking distance to home.

We had to wait about 10 minutes to get our sandwiches but everything was totally fresh and worth the wait. We had the Veggie, Turkey and Fried Chicken sandwiches. I liked the Chicken sandwich the best. Garlic fries were great too. I would definitely visit again.
Sandwiches are awesome.
I'm so grateful for the vegan almond joy sandwich.

Sammies for the world! If you have anything against good bread, we’ll thought out toppings that compliment thick cut meat or veggies then you definitely not want to eat here! If you do like those things, plus some added local love, then please try this place out! I had the dip and my wife had the veggie, both of which were fantastic! Keep slinging those sammies EARL!
Sandwiches are very good!

Friendly staff and some very delicious sandwiches. I like that bread is toasted and that the sandwich portions are healthy and large. I visited with a group and we were all satisfied with some eating 2 sandwiches!

Our favorite place for sandwiches.  This second location just opened so it was not fully staffed and the menu was not a full menu either.  Love the brisket, but what makes their sandwiches awesome is the bread they use and the dip.  Sooooo good!
Very tasty sandwiches!
Amazing array of delicious meat sandwiches and vegetarian options
No garlic fries here or mushroom toast, otherwise good tasting sandwiches
Great sandwiches!!
Our sandwiches were delicious.  Service was quick and friendly.  We will definitely be back!

Got the Po boy, bread was awesome, seasonings and sauce was yum, pickles ok. But the chicken just was so bouncey and flavorless. Plus shaped in a way where it made it difficult to keep it from sliding out. Regardless I'll give it another shot, there is talent in there, just not in the Po boy

Delicious lobster roll
Pork belly marinara.
The bomb dot com

Great sandwiches. I've been wanting to come here since they opened but never got to too now. Better later than never. This place is huge compared to their Kaimuki location. With a little more in the menu. I see a couple of burgers and some other things on the menu. I'll have to come back to try them.
They have a vegan sandwich and a couple of vegetarian ones as well. They will validate your parking if you park in the SALT structure.
Cool people run it, great sandwiches.
I’ll

Oh boy the sandwiches are surprisingly flavorful. At first I thought I had been paying an inordinate amount but it really is worth your money. The portions are large and The Steak is a very good option if you don't know what to get
Sandwiches so good they'll make you wanna slap yo momma
Great food and customer service!
The secret of the sandwich is their sauce. Always leaves my taste buds at a loss!

Best sandwiches I've had on island. Favorites are the chicken po boy, the Drew, and the steak. Potato salad is tasty and cold brew coffee isn't bad at all for 99 cents. Staff is always friendly and the buy 10 get 1 free cards are nice.

I was excited to learn they were opening in Kakaako, as it's more convenient for me than their original Kaimuki location. The quality and service are just as great and friendly. Ample seating and good parking options nearby. As always, come early if you have a particular favorite sandwich, since the crowd favorites tend to sell out quickly. Even if it sells out, just try literally any other sandwich--they're all good. E.A.R.L. is my go-to for delicious, satisfying sandwiches (especially after a good workout).

One of the longest waits for a sandwich that I’ve ever had in my life. The sandwiches are mediocre for the price paid. Maybe they are working out the kinks of a new operation still, but hopefully it improves. Worth a try again!

HUGE sandwiches to fill your belly! If you're hungry and like loaded sandwiches, stop in and try the new E.A.R.L. in Kakaako. There's a range of sandwiches, from vegan to veggie to loaded with meat! Plus every now and then they have different specials too. Sandwiches are anywhere from $10-$14 and won't leave you feeling hungry afterwards.
